# Declarative Navigation

Suzume-client must keep all routing changes declarative. Do not call `useNavigate()` or any function that imperatively pushes/replaces history. Use react-router's components instead.

## Allowed

- `<Link to="...">` for in-app links.
- `<NavLink to="...">` for links that need active state.
- `<Navigate to="..." replace />` for redirects (unauthorized, invalid params, etc.) returned from a render path.

## Wrapping styled components

When a Radix Themes component (e.g. `Button`) needs to navigate, use `asChild` and put a router `Link` inside:

```tsx
<Button asChild size="3" variant="surface">
  <Link to={`/decks/${deckId}/${mode}/${level}`}>{level.toUpperCase()}</Link>
</Button>
```

## Anti-patterns

- Do not call `navigate(...)` inside `onClick`, effects, or event handlers.
- Do not render `<a href="#">` with `preventDefault` to fake a button. If the action only changes local state, use `<Button variant="ghost">`.
- Do not import `useNavigate` from `react-router-dom`.
